    <note type="biography">
        <p>Historian and politician. Appointed assistant commissioner and subsequently government inspector of public works, 1863. Published <hi rend="italic">History of the cotton famine</hi> in 1864. Edited the <hi rend="italic">Echo</hi>, an evening newspaper, 1868–75. MP for Salford, 1880–5. Alderman, London County Council, 1889–1902; chairman, 1895–6. Knighted, 1895.</p></note>
